Gradient

The gradient is the derivative to functions of multiple variables. For a function , the gradient is a vector that contains all the partial derivatives of the function with respect to each variable .


*Source: https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/947604/gradient-tangents-planes-and-steepest-direction

The gradient points in the direction of the steepest ascent of the function, and its magnitude tells you how steep the slope is.
